SUMMARY: The History of Caribbean Music in Toronto
DESCRIPTION:Author\, music historian and cultural critic\, Klive Walker (
 Dubwise: Reasoning from the Reggae Underground)\, presents an overview of
  how Canadians with heritage in the Caribbean have impacted Toronto throu
 gh music – from the 1950s to the 2000s.\n\nReggae\, calypso\, hip-hop and
  rhythm and blues music genres are covered. Some of the main Caribbean-Ca
 nadian personalities and events are presented within a historical context
 . The program illustrates the importance of this music to the Caribbean-C
 anadian community here in Toronto and its powerful influence on the mains
 tream.\n\nPlease visit www.tpl.ca http://www.tpl.ca to register.
CATEGORIES:Community
